sub_title: Product and Process Technologist at Tata Steel
summary: I am an analytical thinker with a thorough theoretical background in physics. Studying geophysics at three different universities, made me familiar with a broad range of geophysics and with working in an international environment. During my PhD, I became an experienced numerical modeler. I am curiosity driven and can reduce complex problems into a set of understandable sub-problems by posing the right questions. While working on a theoretical problem, I always keep the link to the applications. I enjoy explaining, both orally and in written form, my results to a general public. Discussing my results and research strategies with colleagues, keeps me alert and I am open for suggestions for improvement. I am eager to broaden my knowledge.

- electromagnetism
- programing in Fortan, Matlab and using MPI (Message Passing Interface for parallel computing)
- inversion and optimization
- MT fieldwork in Ethiopia 

During my PhD I have been working on the development of a 3-D inversion code for magnetotelluric (MT) data. The newly developed MT inverse code, which I named EMJoy, is written in Fortran 90 and the code is parallelized using the Message Passing Interface (MPI). Within EMJoy, the forward problem is solved using an already existing integral equation based code that was developed in Fortran 77. I completely rewrote this code using Fortran 90. The inverse problem itself is solved using a limited memory quasi-Newton method.
Furthermore, I participated in a MT field survey in Ethiopia. We conducted measurements on Aluto volcano, aiming to map the geothermal system below Aluto. The results of this survey have been published in Geophysical Journal International.
Finally, I investigated, using a forward model, whether inter-site (electric) phase tensors can be utilized to obtain information about the subsurface's conductivity. The results of this study are published in Earth, Planets & Space.", 'title': 'PhD Student', 'employment_type': None}]}, {'company': {'id': 49116, 'name': 'Forschungszentrum Jülich', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C560BAQEwNL-uzlAQcw/company-logo_400_400/0/1519856631063?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=uu9Mo985o7LfZZLslR0FQKK0I2t-k2h5q0dAEwXcGHc', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/forschungszentrum-julich/', 'employees': {'start': 5001, 'end': 10000}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': None, 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}}, 'company': 'Forschungszentrum Jülich', 'description': 'Contiuation of research on M.Sc topic.', 'title': 'Research Assistant', 'employment_type': None}]}, {'company': {'id': 49116, 'name': 'Forschungszentrum Jülich', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C560BAQEwNL-uzlAQcw/company-logo_400_400/0/1519856631063?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=uu9Mo985o7LfZZLslR0FQKK0I2t-k2h5q0dAEwXcGHc', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/forschungszentrum-julich/', 'employees': {'start': 5001, 'end': 10000}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': None, 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}}, 'company': 'Forschungszentrum Jülich', 'description': 'M.Sc. thesis research.
